    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In geology, the fundamental units of lithostratigraphy comprising distinctive assemblages, layers, or units of rock in an area, characterized as being of homogeneous origin and appearance. The designation and limits of a given geological formation may vary, depending upon the criteria imposed by the cataloging body.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
